# Install required libraries in Colab

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import yfinance as yf
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller, coint
from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA
from statsmodels.graphics.tsaplots import plot_acf, plot_pacf
import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")

# Set random seed for reproducibility
np.random.seed(42)

# Step 1: Fetch stock data for USB and PNC from Nov 29, 2019
start_date = "2019-11-29"
end_date = "2025-02-28"

print("Fetching data for USB...")
usb_data = yf.download("USB", start=start_date, end=end_date)
print("Fetching data for PNC...")
pnc_data = yf.download("PNC", start=start_date, end=end_date)

# Extract 'Close' prices (assuming single-column data from yf.download)
usb_prices = usb_data["Close"].dropna()
pnc_prices = pnc_data["Close"].dropna()

# Align indices for cointegration test
combined = pd.concat([usb_prices, pnc_prices], axis=1).dropna()
usb_prices = combined.iloc[:, 0]
pnc_prices = combined.iloc[:, 1]

# Step 2: Simulate a Random Walk
def random_walk_simulation(initial_price, steps, scale=1):
    random_steps = np.random.normal(loc=0, scale=scale, size=steps)
    random_steps[0] = 0
    return initial_price + np.cumsum(random_steps)

usb_rw = random_walk_simulation(usb_prices.iloc[0], len(usb_prices), scale=5)
pnc_rw = random_walk_simulation(pnc_prices.iloc[0], len(pnc_prices), scale=5)

# Step 3: Unit Root Test (ADF)
def unit_root_test(series, name):
    result = adfuller(series.dropna())
    print(f"\nUnit Root Test (ADF) for {name}:")
    print(f"ADF Statistic: {result[0]:.4f}")
    print(f"p-value: {result[1]:.4f}")
    print("Critical Values:", {k: round(v, 4) for k, v in result[4].items()})
    if result[1] > 0.05:
        print(f"{name} likely has a unit root (non-stationary).")
    else:
        print(f"{name} does not have a unit root (stationary).")

usb_returns = usb_prices.pct_change().dropna()
pnc_returns = pnc_prices.pct_change().dropna()

unit_root_test(usb_prices, "USB Prices")
unit_root_test(pnc_prices, "PNC Prices")
unit_root_test(usb_returns, "USB Returns")
unit_root_test(pnc_returns, "PNC Returns")

# Step 4: Fit ARMA Model (ARMA(1,1))
def fit_arma(series, name):
    model = ARIMA(series, order=(1, 0, 1))
    fit = model.fit()
    print(f"\nARMA(1,1) Model Summary for {name}:")
    print(fit.summary().tables[1])
    return fit

usb_arma = fit_arma(usb_returns, "USB Returns")
pnc_arma = fit_arma(pnc_returns, "PNC Returns")

# Step 5: Correlogram and Partial Correlogram of Residuals
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))

plt.subplot(2, 2, 1)
plot_acf(usb_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="ACF of USB ARMA Residuals")
plt.subplot(2, 2, 2)
plot_pacf(usb_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="PACF of USB ARMA Residuals")
plt.subplot(2, 2, 3)
plot_acf(pnc_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="ACF of PNC ARMA Residuals")
plt.subplot(2, 2, 4)
plot_pacf(pnc_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="PACF of PNC ARMA Residuals")
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Step 6: Cointegration Test (Engle-Granger)
print("\nCointegration Test (Engle-Granger) between USB and PNC Prices:")
coint_result = coint(usb_prices, pnc_prices)
print(f"Cointegration Test Statistic: {coint_result[0]:.4f}")
print(f"p-value: {coint_result[1]:.4f}")
print("Critical Values:", {k: round(v, 4) for k, v in zip(['1%', '5%', '10%'], coint_result[2])})
if coint_result[1] < 0.05:
    print("Result: Reject the null hypothesis - USB and PNC prices are cointegrated.")
else:
    print("Result: Fail to reject the null hypothesis - USB and PNC prices are not cointegrated.")

# Step 7: Plotting Original Analyses
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 10))

# Random Walk vs Actual Prices
plt.subplot(3, 1, 1)
plt.plot(usb_prices.index, usb_prices, label="USB Actual", color="blue")
plt.plot(usb_prices.index, usb_rw, label="USB Random Walk", color="orange", linestyle="--")
plt.plot(pnc_prices.index, pnc_prices, label="PNC Actual", color="green")
plt.plot(pnc_prices.index, pnc_rw, label="PNC Random Walk", color="red", linestyle="--")
plt.title("Stock Prices vs Random Walk Simulation")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Price")
plt.legend()

# Returns
plt.subplot(3, 1, 2)
plt.plot(usb_returns.index, usb_returns, label="USB Returns", color="blue")
plt.plot(pnc_returns.index, pnc_returns, label="PNC Returns", color="green")
plt.title("Daily Returns")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Returns")
plt.legend()

# ARMA Forecasts (last 30 days)
usb_forecast = usb_arma.forecast(steps=30)
pnc_forecast = pnc_arma.forecast(steps=30)
forecast_index = pd.date_range(start=usb_returns.index[-1], periods=30, freq="B")

plt.subplot(3, 1, 3)
plt.plot(usb_returns.index[-30:], usb_returns[-30:], label="USB Actual Returns", color="blue")
plt.plot(forecast_index, usb_forecast, label="USB ARMA Forecast", color="orange", linestyle="--")
plt.plot(pnc_returns.index[-30:], pnc_returns[-30:], label="PNC Actual Returns", color="green")
plt.plot(forecast_index, pnc_forecast, label="PNC ARMA Forecast", color="red", linestyle="--")
plt.title("ARMA(1,1) Forecast vs Actual Returns (Last 30 Days)")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Returns")
plt.legend()

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import yfinance as yf
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller, coint
from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA
from statsmodels.graphics.tsaplots import plot_acf, plot_pacf
import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")

# Set random seed for reproducibility
np.random.seed(42)

# Step 1: Fetch stock data for APO and ARES from Nov 29, 2019
start_date = "2019-11-29"
end_date = "2025-02-28"

print("Fetching data for APO...")
apo_data = yf.download("APO", start=start_date, end=end_date)
print("Fetching data for ARES...")
ares_data = yf.download("ARES", start=start_date, end=end_date)

# Extract 'Close' prices (single-column data from yf.download)
apo_prices = apo_data["Close"].dropna()
ares_prices = ares_data["Close"].dropna()

# Align indices for cointegration test
combined = pd.concat([apo_prices, ares_prices], axis=1).dropna()
apo_prices = combined.iloc[:, 0]
ares_prices = combined.iloc[:, 1]

# Step 2: Simulate a Random Walk
def random_walk_simulation(initial_price, steps, scale=1):
    random_steps = np.random.normal(loc=0, scale=scale, size=steps)
    random_steps[0] = 0
    return initial_price + np.cumsum(random_steps)

apo_rw = random_walk_simulation(apo_prices.iloc[0], len(apo_prices), scale=5)
ares_rw = random_walk_simulation(ares_prices.iloc[0], len(ares_prices), scale=5)

# Step 3: Unit Root Test (ADF)
def unit_root_test(series, name):
    result = adfuller(series.dropna())
    print(f"\nUnit Root Test (ADF) for {name}:")
    print(f"ADF Statistic: {result[0]:.4f}")
    print(f"p-value: {result[1]:.4f}")
    print("Critical Values:", {k: round(v, 4) for k, v in result[4].items()})
    if result[1] > 0.05:
        print(f"{name} likely has a unit root (non-stationary).")
    else:
        print(f"{name} does not have a unit root (stationary).")

apo_returns = apo_prices.pct_change().dropna()
ares_returns = ares_prices.pct_change().dropna()

unit_root_test(apo_prices, "APO Prices")
unit_root_test(ares_prices, "ARES Prices")
unit_root_test(apo_returns, "APO Returns")
unit_root_test(ares_returns, "ARES Returns")

# Step 4: Fit ARMA Model (ARMA(1,1))
def fit_arma(series, name):
    model = ARIMA(series, order=(1, 0, 1))
    fit = model.fit()
    print(f"\nARMA(1,1) Model Summary for {name}:")
    print(fit.summary().tables[1])
    return fit

apo_arma = fit_arma(apo_returns, "APO Returns")
ares_arma = fit_arma(ares_returns, "ARES Returns")

# Step 5: Correlogram and Partial Correlogram of Residuals
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))

plt.subplot(2, 2, 1)
plot_acf(apo_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="ACF of APO ARMA Residuals")
plt.subplot(2, 2, 2)
plot_pacf(apo_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="PACF of APO ARMA Residuals")
plt.subplot(2, 2, 3)
plot_acf(ares_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="ACF of ARES ARMA Residuals")
plt.subplot(2, 2, 4)
plot_pacf(ares_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="PACF of ARES ARMA Residuals")
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Step 6: Cointegration Test (Engle-Granger)
print("\nCointegration Test (Engle-Granger) between APO and ARES Prices:")
coint_result = coint(apo_prices, ares_prices)
print(f"Cointegration Test Statistic: {coint_result[0]:.4f}")
print(f"p-value: {coint_result[1]:.4f}")
print("Critical Values:", {k: round(v, 4) for k, v in zip(['1%', '5%', '10%'], coint_result[2])})
if coint_result[1] < 0.05:
    print("Result: Reject the null hypothesis - APO and ARES prices are cointegrated.")
else:
    print("Result: Fail to reject the null hypothesis - APO and ARES prices are not cointegrated.")

# Step 7: Plotting Original Analyses
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 10))

# Random Walk vs Actual Prices
plt.subplot(3, 1, 1)
plt.plot(apo_prices.index, apo_prices, label="APO Actual", color="blue")
plt.plot(apo_prices.index, apo_rw, label="APO Random Walk", color="orange", linestyle="--")
plt.plot(ares_prices.index, ares_prices, label="ARES Actual", color="green")
plt.plot(ares_prices.index, ares_rw, label="ARES Random Walk", color="red", linestyle="--")
plt.title("Stock Prices vs Random Walk Simulation")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Price")
plt.legend()

# Returns
plt.subplot(3, 1, 2)
plt.plot(apo_returns.index, apo_returns, label="APO Returns", color="blue")
plt.plot(ares_returns.index, ares_returns, label="ARES Returns", color="green")
plt.title("Daily Returns")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Returns")
plt.legend()

# ARMA Forecasts (last 30 days)
apo_forecast = apo_arma.forecast(steps=30)
ares_forecast = ares_arma.forecast(steps=30)
forecast_index = pd.date_range(start=apo_returns.index[-1], periods=30, freq="B")

plt.subplot(3, 1, 3)
plt.plot(apo_returns.index[-30:], apo_returns[-30:], label="APO Actual Returns", color="blue")
plt.plot(forecast_index, apo_forecast, label="APO ARMA Forecast", color="orange", linestyle="--")
plt.plot(ares_returns.index[-30:], ares_returns[-30:], label="ARES Actual Returns", color="green")
plt.plot(forecast_index, ares_forecast, label="ARES ARMA Forecast", color="red", linestyle="--")
plt.title("ARMA(1,1) Forecast vs Actual Returns (Last 30 Days)")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Returns")
plt.legend()
